$l = random(2,5,1);
$a = random(2,5,1);
$b = $l * $a;

BEGIN_TEXT
The Riemann sum
\[ \sum_{k=1}^{$b} \left( \left(\frac{k}{$l}\right)^2 
+1\right) \frac{1}{$l} \]
estimates the area under the curve \(y=f(x)\) above the 
interval \( [a,b]\) using right end points.  
  
END_TEXT



BEGIN_TEXT
